Hey. Sis.

9
00:06:55,489 --> 00:06:56,649
What time is it!

10
00:06:56,724 --> 00:06:58,385
Just after 8:00.

11
00:06:58,592 --> 00:06:59,752
You want me to make coffee!

12
00:06:59,827 --> 00:07:02,421
No. I gotta go. I'll call you later.

13
00:07:02,930 --> 00:07:04,921
You sure there's nothing I can do!

14
00:07:04,999 --> 00:07:08,560
Angie. Everything's gonna be fine.
Just go back to sleep.

15
00:07:51,846 --> 00:07:54,144
All right, I'm coming, I'm coming.

16
00:07:58,185 --> 00:07:59,516
Ben Carson.

17
00:07:59,587 --> 00:08:03,785
Lorenzo Sapelli. I've been waiting for you.
Come on in.

18
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:04,847
Thanks.

19
00:08:11,565 --> 00:08:13,032
How long you been working here!

20
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:16,900
All together! Fifteen years.

21
00:08:18,339 --> 00:08:20,204
You were here for the fire!

22
00:08:21,342 --> 00:08:22,673
Devastating.

23
00:08:24,278 --> 00:08:27,145
Entire building up in flames.

24
00:08:37,057 --> 00:08:39,753
It has been five years since the fire.

25
00:08:39,827 --> 00:08:43,558
They're still in a legal battle
with the insurance companies.

26
00:08:43,631 --> 00:08:47,089
Even cleaning up this mess is impossible.

27
00:08:47,168 --> 00:08:50,331
I've given up faith about reopening.
And besides.

28
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:54,306
Who'd ever want to shop here
after everything that's happened!

29
00:08:55,209 --> 00:08:58,178
You know. The Meredith family
acquired this building

30
00:08:58,245 --> 00:09:01,840
after St. Matthew's Hospital
closed in 1952.

31
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:06,247
It was the very first Mayflower
to open on the East Coast.

32
00:09:08,155 --> 00:09:12,615
Yeah. The company wants us to patrol
the premises every couple of hours.

33
00:09:12,693 --> 00:09:16,527
But I do my rounds every three.
That's more than enough.

34
00:09:16,597 --> 00:09:21,432
Anyway. You'll see. Not too much
going on. It's pretty calm around here.

35
00:09:24,805 --> 00:09:27,399
Well. There you go.

36
00:09:28,142 --> 00:09:31,873
Perfume and cosmetics department.
What's left of it anyway.

37
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:41,013
Thank God you didn't show up any later.
This place gives me the creeps at night.

38
00:09:41,088 --> 00:09:42,646
No electricity.

39
