Yes. What is it!

252
00:39:41,353 --> 00:39:44,845
There's someone in the lobby for you.
It sounds urgent.

253
00:39:53,399 --> 00:39:54,661
Ben.

254
00:39:54,733 --> 00:39:56,064
What's happening!
What are you doing here!

255
00:39:56,135 --> 00:39:58,968
Thanks for seeing me.
Look. I need to ask you a favor.

256
00:39:59,038 --> 00:40:01,666
- I'm in the middle of work.
- I know. Twenty minutes.

257
00:40:01,740 --> 00:40:03,935
Yesterday morning you picked up a body.

258
00:40:04,009 --> 00:40:07,069
Gary Lewis.
I just need to take a look at him.

259
00:40:07,546 --> 00:40:08,843
- Who is he!
- He was a night watchman

260
00:40:08,914 --> 00:40:11,212
at the Mayflower. I replaced him.

261
00:40:11,283 --> 00:40:12,750
How do you have his driver's license!

262
00:40:12,818 --> 00:40:16,811
I found his wallet in the department store.
Look. I just need to know how he died.

263
00:40:17,623 --> 00:40:19,591
Why do you need to know how he died!

264
00:40:19,658 --> 00:40:22,422
Ben. You've been suspended. You're not
supposed to be doing any investigations.

265
00:40:22,494 --> 00:40:24,553
Amy. Please. Just listen to me.
This is serious.

266
00:40:24,630 --> 00:40:27,531
There are some very strange things
happening over at the Mayflower.

267
00:40:27,599 --> 00:40:29,726
I can't explain. But it's...

268
00:40:30,869 --> 00:40:33,838
This guy Gary Lewis sent me a package
right before he died.

269
00:40:33,906 --> 00:40:35,874
Thing is. I never met him before.

270
00:40:35,941 --> 00:40:39,104
Inside the package were all these articles
on the Mayflower. On the fire.

271
00:40:39,178 --> 00:40:42,807
It was like he was trying to tell me
something or warn me about something.

272
00:40:42,881 --> 00:40:45,076
I need to figure this out. Please.

273
00:40:45,150 --> 00:40:48,813
B-16
Gary Lewis. Gary Lewis. There he is. B-16.

274
00:40:49,421 --> 00:40:50,683
He slashed his throat.

275
00:40:50,756 --> 00:40:54,089
There you go. There's your answer.
Your man committed suicide.

276
00:40:54,159 --> 00:40:58,789
And you get a lot of suicide cases
with people that slash their own throats!

277
00:40:59,698 --> 00:41:02,690
I didn't think so. Excuse me.

278
00:41:02,768 --> 00:41:06,067
All I know is.
The police are still investigating this one.

279
00:41:06,138 --> 00:41:07,435
That's why we still have the body.

280
00:41:07,506 --> 00:41:10,031
What did he use to cut his throat!

281
00:41:10,109 --> 00:41:11,940
A piece of mirror.

282
00:41:13,278 --> 00:41:15,109
He probably broke the mirror into pieces

283
00:41:15,180 --> 00:41:17,842
so he'd have something
to cut himself with.

284
00:41:17,916 --> 00:41:19,747
Seven years bad luck.

285
00:41:21,687 --> 00:41:23,279
Esseker.

286
00:41:23,355 --> 00:41:25,186
Are you okay. Ben!

287
00:41:25,891 --> 00:41:27,222
I'm fine.

288
00:41:30,229 --> 00:41:32,163
I'm sorry. Excuse me.

289
00:41:35,367 --> 00:41:37,301
I need to see his file.

290
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:39,234
- What!
- I need his file.

291
00:41:39,304 --> 00:41:40,328
- Ben.
- What's the problem!

292
00:41:40,405 --> 00:41:41,463
I just need to see his file.

293
00:41:41,540 --> 00:41:43,371
Calm down. You're not even
supposed to be down here.

294
00:41:43,442 --> 00:41:45,706
And now you want to
look at somebody's file!

295
00:41:45,777 --> 00:41:47,608
Look. I'll be off then.

296
00:41:47,679 --> 00:41:49,909
Amy. You know where to find me
if you need me.

297
00:41:49,982 --> 00:41:52,610
Yeah. Thanks. Peter. I appreciate it.

298
00:41:57,856 --> 00:42:01,690
- I want you to leave now. I'm serious. Ben.
- Amy. I'm sorry.

299
00:42:02,094 --> 00:42:04,858
I can't leave here until I see that file.

300
00:42:05,364 --> 00:42:07,423
It's important. Please.

301
00:42:08,800 --> 00:42:10,097
Please.

302
00:42:38,263 --> 00:42:41,426
Amy. Come here and look at this picture.

303
00:42:45,103 --> 00:42:47,628
Look at the piece of mirror
that Gary Lewis is holding.

304
00:42:47,706 --> 00:42:51,767
And look at it up here
in its reflected image in the other mirror.

305
00:42:52,878 --> 00:42:54,675
It's full of blood.

306
00:42:54,746 --> 00:42:58,705
Yet in reality. It's perfectly clean.
Not a single drop. Not a single drop on it.

307
00:42:58,784 --> 00:43:01,218
So what! It's probably the angle
from which the photograph was taken.

308
00:43:01,286 --> 00:43:03,311
What are you trying to prove!

309
00:43:03,388 --> 00:43:06,221
What if the mirrors are showing us
something that's not really happening!

310
00:43:06,291 --> 00:43:08,953
- What are you talking about!
- No. Just listen to me.

311
00:43:09,027 --> 00:43:13,828
What if the mirrors are reflecting
something that's beyond our reality!

312
00:43:13,899 --> 00:43:16,493
What if the mirrors can actually make us
do things that we don't want to do!

313
00:43:16,568 --> 00:43:18,263
Like making Gary Lewis
slit his own throat.

314
00:43:18,337 --> 00:43:22,171
Ben. Listen to yourself.
You can't talk like that around here.

315
00:43:22,241 --> 00:43:24,402
Don't you want to get reinstated!

316
00:43:24,476 --> 00:43:28,310
Amy. I'm seeing things in the mirrors
at work. Bad things.

317
00:43:28,380 --> 00:43:30,610
To the point where I can feel
what they're showing me.

318
00:43:30,682 --> 00:43:34,482
Ben. You're driving me fucking crazy!
I don't have time for this.

319
00:43:34,553 --> 00:43:35,679
What's wrong with you!

320
00:43:35,754 --> 00:43:39,656
Do you think I'm making this up!
Do you think I'm fucking lying!

321
00:43:42,127 --> 00:43:45,460
What medication are you taking
to stop drinking!

322
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:03,945
That's a strong drug.

323
00:44:04,516 --> 00:44:09,044
It has a lot of serious side effects.
How many pills are you taking a day!

324
00:44:12,557 --> 00:44:14,923
I'm sorry that I bothered you.

325
00:44:15,694 --> 00:44:17,127
You're right.

326
00:44:18,397 --> 00:44:20,422
Thanks for trying to help.

327
00:46:28,727 --> 00:46:30,820
...night at this bar.
It's a couple of blocks from here.

328
00:46:30,896 --> 00:46:33,057
- All right. Where's the body!
- Calm down.

329
00:46:33,131 --> 00:46:35,793
- I can't. How am I gonna calm down!
- Let the detective by. Step over here.

330
00:46:35,867 --> 00:46:38,768
And there's a guy been living with her
at her place. There's a guy.

331
00:46:38,837 --> 00:46:42,398
All right. You say she works at this bar!
At night!

332
00:46:42,474 --> 00:46:44,465
Yeah. She works nights. She goes nights.

333
00:46:44,543 --> 00:46:46,875
She comes home late.
I don't see her come home.

334
00:46:46,945 --> 00:46:48,469
She probably closes the bar. Right!

335
00:46:48,547 --> 00:46:52,108
Yeah. 'Cause she sleeps during the day.
Like early morning hours.

336
00:46:52,183 --> 00:46:53,548
All right.

337
00:47:19,277 --> 00:47:23,873
I saw blood falling from the ceiling.
Then she call me.

338
00:47:23,949 --> 00:47:27,316
I want you to ask her.
Did she hear any noises. Any sounds!

339
00:47:27,385 --> 00:47:28,579
- What's going on!
- One second.

340
00:47:28,653 --> 00:47:31,349
It's all right. I live in apartment eight.
I used to be a cop.

341
00:47:31,423 --> 00:47:33,983
- Just tell me what's going on.
- Just a second.

342
00:47:34,059 --> 00:47:37,119
I want to talk to the lead detective!
Angela!

343
00:47:37,195 --> 00:47:40,221
- Who is the lead detective!
- Ben.

344
00:47:40,632 --> 00:47:43,396
Larry. What the hell are you doing here!

345
00:47:44,135 --> 00:47:47,696
- Larry. Just tell me what's going on.
- Ben. It's not good.

346
00:47:47,772 --> 00:47:49,399
Where's Angie!

347
00:47:51,176 --> 00:47:54,270
Where the fuck is my sister!
Tell them to let go of me!

348
00:47:54,346 --> 00:47:56,746
- I can't do that. Ben!
- God damn it!

349
00:48:40,358 --> 00:48:43,191
The water has obliterated
most of the marks.

350
00:48:43,461 --> 00:48:46,294
No sign of struggle or forced entry.

351
00:48:46,798 --> 00:48:50,199
And the front door was locked.
Which means that

352
00:48:50,268 --> 00:48:52,361
the person who did this
either had keys to the apartment

353
00:48:52,437 --> 00:48:54,667
or it was someone that she knew.

354
00:48:54,739 --> 00:48:57,435
He would've never laid a finger on her.

355
00:48:58,209 --> 00:49:01,906
You know. When their father died.
Ben took care of Angela.

356
00:49:04,349 --> 00:49:05,407
She meant the world to him.

357
00:49:05,483 --> 00:49:09,442
Listen. So far. His statement is pretty
consistent with the facts. You know!

358
00:49:09,521 --> 00:49:12,513
We checked it out.
He showed up to work at 7:00 p.m.

359
00:49:12,590 --> 00:49:13,818
And the downstairs neighbors said

360
00:49:13,892 --> 00:49:17,089
they began to notice the water leakage
at around 10:00.

361
00:49:17,162 --> 00:49:20,222
The only strange thing.
And this could just be a coincidence.

362
00:49:20,298 --> 00:49:24,234
Is that Ben told the daytime
security guard. Lorenzo Sapelli.

363
00:49:24,302 --> 00:49:27,066
That he was planning on quitting the job.

364
00:49:27,138 --> 00:49:31,802
Like he was moving away someplace.
He mention anything like that to you!

365
00:49:31,876 --> 00:49:33,036
No.

366
00:49:34,379 --> 00:49:37,712
Lately. Communication hasn't been
our strong point.

367
00:49:38,316 --> 00:49:39,544
What are you gonna do with him!

368
00:49:39,617 --> 00:49:41,608
I figure we'll let him go.
We got no reason to keep him here.

369
00:49:41,686 --> 00:49:43,017
Larry.

370
00:49:55,867 --> 00:49:57,528
I'm so sorry.

371
00:49:59,104 --> 00:50:00,628
Ben!

372
00:50:00,705 --> 00:50:03,640
Why don't you come home
and spend some days with the kids!

373
00:50:03,708 --> 00:50:05,232
I can't.

374
00:50:06,044 --> 00:50:09,013
I don't want to put our children in danger.

375
00:50:10,048 --> 00:50:12,608
She asked me to quit. But I wouldn't.

376
00:50:13,918 --> 00:50:17,786
- They came after her.
- What are you talking about!

377
00:50:20,658 --> 00:50:23,354
I've got some things I need to take care of.

378
00:50:23,428 --> 00:50:26,556
- Wait. Ben. Please.
- Amy. Amy. Let me go.

379
00:50:26,631 --> 00:50:28,121
I don't want you
to get in any more trouble.

380
00:50:28,199 --> 00:50:31,726
- Please stay out of it.
- I know who did this.

381
00:50:31,803 --> 00:50:35,364
Well. In that case.
You've got to tell Larry everything.

382
00:50:37,942 --> 00:50:39,933
He'll never believe me.

383
00:50:41,646 --> 00:50:43,307
Neither will you.

384
00:52:05,463 --> 00:52:07,488
What do you want!

385
00:52:07,565 --> 00:52:09,430
Please. Just tell me.

386
00:52:10,134 --> 00:52:12,364
What do you want from me!

387
00:52:17,275 --> 00:52:19,743
What do you want from me!

388
00:52:40,265 --> 00:52:42,290
"Esseker."

389
00:52:47,105 --> 00:52:50,802
Hey. I need you to run a name for me.
Esseker.

390
00:52:50,875 --> 00:52:55,744
Echo. Sierra. Sierra. Echo.
Kilo. Echo. Romeo.

391
00:52:55,813 --> 00:52:59,305
- Did you check online?
- I've already done that.

392
00:52:59,384 --> 00:53:01,944
Nothing. IRS and DMV.

393
00:53:02,020 --> 00:53:03,885
- Where?
- Try New York.

394
00:53:03,955 --> 00:53:05,582
- When?
- Last five or six years.

395
00:53:05,657 --> 00:53:06,988
Okay, Ben.

396
00:53:07,058 --> 00:53:09,583
Thanks.
Get back to me as soon as you can.

397
00:53:11,396 --> 00:53:14,263
"Mayflower burns. 48 presumed dead."

398
00:53:16,467 --> 00:53:19,265
"Berry confesses to
deadly Mayflower fire."

399
00:53:24,609 --> 00:53:26,543
"Watchman arrested."

400
00:53:28,680 --> 00:53:32,480
"Woman. Three children murdered."
Come on. Ben. Connect the dots.

401
00:53:32,550 --> 00:53:34,814
"Mr. Berry maintains that
the mirrors in the store are the ones

402
00:53:34,886 --> 00:53:38,049
"that brutally killed his wife
and three children."

403
00:53:42,393 --> 00:53:45,123
"Mirrors are guilty. Mirrors are guilty."

404
00:53:45,830 --> 00:53:48,321
- Yeah. What did you get!
- Hey.

405
00:53:48,399 --> 00:53:51,232
Look, I didn't find anything
under that name.

406
00:53:51,302 --> 00:53:53,896
Shit! Shit.

407
00:53:53,972 --> 00:53:56,532
Do you want me
to look outside New York?

408
00:53:56,607 --> 00:53:59,201
No. Hold on. Hold on.

409
00:54:03,114 --> 00:54:06,675
I want you to run another name for me.
Berry. Terrence Berry.

410
00:54:06,751 --> 00:54:09,219
Terrence Berry.

411
00:54:10,154 --> 00:54:11,382
Wait one sec.

412
00:54:14,659 --> 00:54:18,117
- I think I got him. You still there?
- Yeah.

413
00:54:18,930 --> 00:54:22,388
- Your guy murdered his whole family.
- I already know that.

414
00:54:22,467 --> 00:54:23,866
He's dead.

415
00:54:25,403 --> 00:54:26,734
Damn it.

416
00:54:28,473 --> 00:54:31,306
Can you tell me where he was committed
before he died!

417
00:54:34,245 --> 00:54:37,544
You know. Mr. Carson. When one
starts to perceive one's own reflection

418
00:54:37,615 --> 00:54:39,480
as a completely separate being.

419
00:54:39,550 --> 00:54:42,747
One is suddenly confronted
with two entirely separate egos.

420
00:54:42,820 --> 00:54:46,517
Two entirely separate worlds
that can surface at any given moment.

421
00:54:46,591 --> 00:54:49,890
A feeling of self-hatred.
Usually triggered by a psychological shock

422
00:54:49,961 --> 00:54:51,792
can split the personality in two.

423
00:54:51,863 --> 00:54:55,162
Hence creating two or more personalities
with distinct memories

424
00:54:55,233 --> 00:54:58,828
and distinct behavior patterns
within the same individual.

425
00:54:58,903 --> 00:55:03,306
The patient then has
the false perception of the existence

426
00:55:03,374 --> 00:55:07,640
of two distinct worlds. The real world
and the world inside a mirror.

427
00:55:12,483 --> 00:55:15,145
These recordings were used
in Terrence's trial.

428
00:55:18,456 --> 00:55:20,321
You'll see they speak for themselves.

429
00:55:24,629 --> 00:55:26,563
Why did you set
the department store on fire?

430
00:55:26,631 --> 00:55:29,794
In order to destroy the mirrors.

431
00:55:31,736 --> 00:55:35,297
Only fire can destroy mirrors,
isn't that right, Doctor?

432
00:55:36,407 --> 00:55:40,901
What made you think you absolutely
had to destroy those mirrors, Terrence?

433
00:55:44,549 --> 00:55:49,486
They killed my Helen
and my three children.

434
00:55:50,254 --> 00:55:51,653
For what reason?

435
00:55:51,722 --> 00:55:53,121
Why would mirrors
want to kill your family?

436
00:55:53,191 --> 00:55:55,887
- Because I didn't...
- Didn't do what?

437
00:55:58,329 --> 00:56:00,058
They asked me to find Esseker.

438
00:56:00,131 --> 00:56:01,155
Oh. My God.

439
00:56:01,232 --> 00:56:03,029
We all are looking for Esseker.

440
00:56:03,101 --> 00:56:04,796
Amy.

441
00:56:04,869 --> 00:56:06,928
Excuse me. I have to go.

442
00:56:08,272 --> 00:56:12,902
Tell me about Esseker, Terrence.
Who is Esseker?

443
00:56:12,977 --> 00:56:15,639
I don't know who Esseker is!

444
00:56:16,681 --> 00:56:19,343
I don't know who Esseker is!

445
00:56:20,985 --> 00:56:22,282
I don't know.

446
00:56:30,595 --> 00:56:32,722
Mrs. Carson! It's Rosa.

447
00:56:33,397 --> 00:56:38,266
Mr. Ben is here.
He's moving all of the furniture around.

448
00:57:11,536 --> 00:57:14,300
- Hey. How was school today!
- Good.

449
00:57:14,372 --> 00:57:16,636
Good. I'll be right back.

450
00:57:28,252 --> 00:57:29,276
Dad...

451
00:57:29,353 --> 00:57:32,982
Sweetheart. Just give me a second.
I gotta take care of a couple of things.

452
00:57:55,513 --> 00:57:57,606
Daddy. What are you doing!

453
00:58:00,484 --> 00:58:02,782
Honey. Don't look scared.
Everything's fine.

454
00:58:02,853 --> 00:58:05,754
I think it looks nicer like this. Don't you!

455
00:58:22,206 --> 00:58:24,299
Rosa. What's happening!

456
00:58:24,609 --> 00:58:27,806
Take the kids downstairs. Right now.
Right now.

457
00:58:28,346 --> 00:58:29,438
What the hell are you doing!

458
00:58:29,513 --> 00:58:31,708
Amy. You're gonna have to trust me.
This is for your own protection.

459
00:58:31,782 --> 00:58:34,148
Get out of the house. Right now!

460
00:58:34,252 --> 00:58:37,312
Hey. Are you listening to me!
You are scaring the kids!

461
00:58:37,388 --> 00:58:38,878
If you don't leave immediately.
I'm calling the police.

462
00:58:38,956 --> 00:58:40,924
And I warn you.
You will never see your kids again!

463
00:58:40,992 --> 00:58:43,358
Amy. I am not crazy.
These mirrors are dangerous.

464
00:58:43,427 --> 00:58:46,419
At first I thought it was just the ones
in the store. But after Angela was killed.

465
00:58:46,497 --> 00:58:47,794
I realized they can get at you anywhere.

466
00:58:47,865 --> 00:58:51,801
I promise I will leave the house.
Just let me cover these damn mirrors.

467
00:58:51,869 --> 00:58:53,803
What's wrong with you!

468
00:58:55,006 --> 00:58:57,099
I know what you've been going through
hasn't been easy.

469
00:58:57,174 --> 00:59:00,769
But guess what!
It hasn't been easy for us. Either!

470
00:59:00,845 --> 00:59:03,837
Angela was a part of our lives. Too.
You know that!

471
00:59:03,914 --> 00:59:06,747
It's not fair what you're doing to us. Ben!

472
00:59:06,817 --> 00:59:10,583
Michael... He's acting so strange now.

473
00:59:10,655 --> 00:59:14,682
He always wants to be alone. He won't
talk to me. He's having nightmares.

474
00:59:14,759 --> 00:59:17,626
Ben. Your behavior is rubbing off on him!

475
00:59:17,695 --> 00:59:20,630
He is six years old. I have to protect him!

476
00:59:20,865 --> 00:59:23,095
I want to show you something.

477
00:59:25,903 --> 00:59:27,495
- Ben. Let go of me!
- You don't want to believe me!

478
00:59:27,571 --> 00:59:28,595
Fine. I'll show you.

479
00:59:28,673 --> 00:59:31,164
- What are you doing!
- I'll show you!

480
00:59:32,777 --> 00:59:34,267
Are you crazy!

481
00:59:36,580 --> 00:59:38,741
- Have you gone completely mad!
- Just wait. You'll see.

482
00:59:38,816 --> 00:59:40,681
- See what!
- You'll see.

483
00:59:41,319 --> 00:59:44,311
See what. Ben!
What am I supposed to see!

484
00:59:52,330 --> 00:59:54,093
It's not happening.

485
00:59:55,132 --> 00:59:56,929
It's not happening.

486
00:59:57,134 --> 00:59:59,932
Amy. I swear to you. At the Mayflower...

487
01:00:03,007 --> 01:00:04,872
I am not lying.

488
01:00:20,691 --> 01:00:23,785
Ben. Let's go back inside. Okay!

489
01:00:27,331 --> 01:00:29,162
Put the gun away.

490
01:00:31,268 --> 01:00:34,704
Listen to me. Baby. I want to help you.

491
01:00:35,172 --> 01:00:36,799
Tell the kids I'm sorry.

492
01:00:36,874 --> 01:00:38,102
Ben!

493
01:01:10,207 --> 01:01:11,265
No!

494
01:04:59,069 --> 01:05:00,627
Jesus Christ.

495
01:05:53,791 --> 01:05:55,816
Larry. It's me. I need your help again.

496
01:05:55,893 --> 01:05:59,454
I'm trying to locate the patient-employee
manifest for St. Matthew's Hospital.

497
01:05:59,530 --> 01:06:00,792
Where is it?

498
01:06:00,864 --> 01:06:03,059
Where was it! They closed it down.

499
01:06:03,133 --> 01:06:05,328
But it was in New York.
It's where the Mayflower used to be.

500
01:06:05,402 --> 01:06:07,495
The Mayflower? The department store?

501
01:06:07,571 --> 01:06:09,869
Do you have any idea where
they would store records for a hospital

502
01:06:09,940 --> 01:06:12,135
that's been closed for over 50 years!

503
01:06:12,209 --> 01:06:14,677
No, I don't. But I can send someone
to city hall to check it out.

504
01:06:14,745 --> 01:06:18,681
If it's a public hospital, there'd be a record
of it. Tell me exactly what you need.

505
01:06:18,749 --> 01:06:22,378
Same thing. I'm looking for a patient
or an employee with the name Esseker.

506
01:06:22,453 --> 01:06:27,049
All right, I'm on it. Give me a couple hours,
and, Ben, keep your head down.

507
01:06:49,947 --> 01:06:50,971
Hey.

508
01:06:51,048 --> 01:06:53,516
- Did you get it!
- Yeah. I think so.

509
01:06:54,318 --> 01:06:57,344
It's Anna Esseker.

510
01:06:59,022 --> 01:07:01,286
I didn't really know what you wanted.
So I got all the medical files.

511
01:07:01,358 --> 01:07:04,418
This is perfect. Larry. This is perfect.

512
01:07:04,495 --> 01:07:07,362
What happened!
Did you get in an accident!

513
01:07:07,431 --> 01:07:09,626
Anna Esseker's file.
Did you have to go to city hall for it!

514
01:07:09,700 --> 01:07:11,099
No. I didn't have to go anywhere.

515
01:07:11,168 --> 01:07:14,137
All the files in that place were in storage
with the cold-case evidence.

516
01:07:14,204 --> 01:07:15,364
Why. Because of the fire!

517
01:07:15,439 --> 01:07:19,102
No. It's before the fire.
It's a totally different case.

518
01:07:19,777 --> 01:07:21,438
Anna was a patient at St. Matthew's.

519
01:07:21,512 --> 01:07:24,140
She was in the psych ward
run by a Dr. Kane.

520
01:07:24,214 --> 01:07:27,342
Now get this.
She was only 12 years old when she died.

521
01:07:27,417 --> 01:07:28,406
What!

522
01:07:28,485 --> 01:07:32,444
When the nurses went on their rounds
first thing in the morning. October 6. 1952.

523
01:07:32,523 --> 01:07:35,515
They discovered that all the patients
had left their rooms during the night.

524
01:07:35,592 --> 01:07:37,583
And they'd all gathered in the main hall.

525
01:07:37,661 --> 01:07:40,255
Ben. They were all dead. Including the girl.

526
01:07:40,330 --> 01:07:43,822
Apparently. They killed each other.
I mean. It was a slaughterhouse.

527
01:07:43,901 --> 01:07:46,267
That's when they closed the place down.
Who knows what really happened!

528
01:07:46,336 --> 01:07:48,702
- What about the doctor! Kane!
- Well. They arrested him.

529
01:07:48,772 --> 01:07:50,637
They found him dead
first day of the hearing.

530
01:07:50,707 --> 01:07:54,165
He slashed his wrists
with a piece of the cell mirror.

531
01:07:55,445 --> 01:07:58,107
- Thanks for your help.
- Good luck.

532
01:08:04,354 --> 01:08:05,582
Damn it!

533
01:08:42,459 --> 01:08:43,756
Jesus.

534
01:08:59,977 --> 01:09:01,638
"October 6. 1952."

535
01:09:06,116 --> 01:09:09,643
"Anna Esseker is diagnosed with
severe schizophrenia.

536
01:09:09,720 --> 01:09:14,020
"Leading to withdrawal from reality.
Delusional and violent behavior."

537
01:09:24,868 --> 01:09:27,496
"Pennsylvania. August 1951."

538
01:09:46,223 --> 01:09:47,690
They don't match.

539
01:09:49,927 --> 01:09:54,057
Anna Esseker was discharged
from St. Matthew's Hospital October 4.

540
01:09:54,131 --> 01:09:56,292
Two days before the massacre.

541
01:10:18,555 --> 01:10:20,785
She's alive. Isn't she!

542
01:10:35,372 --> 01:10:38,739
You almost done. Sweetie! Okay.

543
01:10:38,809 --> 01:10:43,246
Why is Daddy acting so scared!
It's not normal.

544
01:10:44,815 --> 01:10:47,613
He's way older than me.

545
01:10:48,185 --> 01:10:51,746
And I'm not acting scared. But he is.

546
01:10:53,023 --> 01:10:57,653
- Doesn't make any sense.
- Michael! What are you doing!

547
01:10:58,729 --> 01:10:59,923
Nothing.

548
01:11:00,764 --> 01:11:04,427
- Okay. Well. We gotta get going. All right!
- Okay.

549
01:11:37,534 --> 01:11:40,025
- Amy! Amy. What's wrong!
- Ben.

550
01:11:40,103 --> 01:11:42,936
You have to come
to the house right now.

551
01:11:43,006 --> 01:11:44,598
I'm so scared.

552
01:11:44,674 --> 01:11:47,575
- Amy, what's wrong?
- I'm so scared.

553
01:11:47,644 --> 01:11:50,875
- Amy. Just tell me what happened.
- There's something in the house.

554
01:11:52,449 --> 01:11:55,077
- Something in the mirrors.
- I'm on my way.

555
01:11:55,719 --> 01:11:57,209
God damn it!

556
01:12:03,660 --> 01:12:04,888
Come on.

557
01:12:55,612 --> 01:13:01,244
- Dad! When are you coming back home!
- Really soon. Sweetheart. Come here.

558
01:13:04,554 --> 01:13:07,250
- I love you. Daddy.
- I love you. Too. Sweetheart.

559
01:13:07,324 --> 01:13:08,882
I gotta go.

560
01:13:09,392 --> 01:13:11,189
I'm afraid to stay here.

561
01:13:11,261 --> 01:13:13,229
There's gonna be windows and mirrors
wherever you go.

562
01:13:13,296 --> 01:13:15,730
Anything that causes a reflection
right now is dangerous.

563
01:13:15,799 --> 01:13:17,824
At least inside the house
we've covered everything.

564
01:13:17,901 --> 01:13:20,062
It's the safest place to be.

565
01:13:20,971 --> 01:13:22,097
Amy. I'm so sorry.

566
01:13:22,239 --> 01:13:25,697
No. It's not your fault.
I should've believed you.

567
01:13:27,444 --> 01:13:28,775
Come here.

568
01:13:32,716 --> 01:13:35,742
Ben. You do whatever it takes to end this.

569
01:13:36,920 --> 01:13:39,354
- You hear me!
- I will.

570
01:13:41,358 --> 01:13:43,155
I'll be right back.

571
01:15:38,808 --> 01:15:40,366
Jesus.

572
01:15:42,412 --> 01:15:43,936
Yes. Sir!

573
01:15:44,014 --> 01:15:47,506
Excuse me. Is this the Esseker farm!

574
01:15:47,584 --> 01:15:50,280
- What is it. Jimmy!
- I don't know. Ma.

575
01:15:50,854 --> 01:15:55,018
- What can I do for you. Sir!
- I'm looking for Anna. Anna Esseker.

576
01:15:55,725 --> 01:15:58,353
There's a man looking for...
You said Anna!

577
01:15:58,428 --> 01:16:00,055
Yes. Anna Esseker.

578
01:16:00,130 --> 01:16:02,064
An Anna Esseker. Ma.

579
01:16:03,833 --> 01:16:07,667
Look. I'm sorry to bother you.
I must have the wrong place.

580
01:16:09,172 --> 01:16:10,503
What is it you want with Anna Esseker!

581
01:16:18,415 --> 01:16:21,248
I'm doing a research paper
on schizophrenia.

582
01:16:21,318 --> 01:16:23,912
I became familiar with
Anna Esseker's case.

583
01:16:23,987 --> 01:16:26,319
I just wanted to ask her some questions.

584
01:16:27,757 --> 01:16:31,523
Go tell Grandpa there's a man here
who's asking about his sister.

585
01:16:31,594 --> 01:16:32,788
Okay.

586
01:16:33,430 --> 01:16:34,897
Thank you.

587
01:16:34,964 --> 01:16:36,261
Grandpa!

588
01:16:37,901 --> 01:16:40,096
You know. Up to this day.

589
01:16:40,170 --> 01:16:43,571
Visions of Anna's fits
still haunt me at night.

590
01:16:45,041 --> 01:16:49,944
I helped my father fix up this part
of the basement especially for her.

591
01:16:52,082 --> 01:16:54,050
Her fits were too violent.

592
01:16:54,117 --> 01:16:57,018
My mother couldn't
take her screams anymore.

593
01:17:05,228 --> 01:17:10,689
We had every priest. Doctor. Healer.
Coming in from all over the county.

594
01:17:10,767 --> 01:17:12,735
But no one could help her.

595
01:17:26,682 --> 01:17:33,520
So finally. A Dr. Kane from New York
answered my parents' cries for help.

596
01:17:35,725 --> 01:17:39,661
He rejected the idea of demonic
possession. Said he didn't believe in it.

597
01:17:39,729 --> 01:17:44,359
He was convinced Anna suffered from
a rare form of personality disorder

598
01:17:45,535 --> 01:17:47,901
and mirrors could help her.

599
01:17:48,805 --> 01:17:52,297
He wanted Anna under his care.
At St. Matthew's.

600
01:17:53,342 --> 01:17:55,469
My parents were very poor.

601
01:17:55,545 --> 01:17:58,946
But he agreed to cover all the costs
of the hospital.

602
01:17:59,482 --> 01:18:01,575
Where did she go after the hospital!

603
01:18:01,651 --> 01:18:03,050
Don't you know!

604
01:18:03,119 --> 01:18:05,747
She died there
with all of Kane's other patients.

605
01:18:05,822 --> 01:18:08,256
Mr. Esseker. I read the file.

606
01:18:08,324 --> 01:18:11,054
Anna left the hospital
two days before the massacre.

607
01:18:11,127 --> 01:18:14,619
Dr. Kane altered the documents
so she could disappear.

608
01:18:16,766 --> 01:18:18,290
Where did you get that document!

609
01:18:18,367 --> 01:18:21,825
I need you to tell me where she went
after St. Matthew's.

610
01:18:22,538 --> 01:18:24,904
She came back
and stayed with us for a while.

611
01:18:24,974 --> 01:18:29,240
What do you mean for a while!
What happened! Why did she leave!

612
01:18:29,312 --> 01:18:32,076
- I don't want to talk about that.
- Why did she leave!

613
01:18:33,583 --> 01:18:36,313
Because strange things
started to happen in the house.

614
01:18:36,385 --> 01:18:37,409
With Anna!

615
01:18:37,486 --> 01:18:40,944
No. No. Not with Anna anymore.
No. She was totally cured.

616
01:18:42,992 --> 01:18:46,519
Strange things started to happen
with the mirrors. Didn't they!

617
01:18:46,596 --> 01:18:49,895
Mr. Esseker. I need to know where Anna
is now. It's a matter of life and death.

618
01:18:49,966 --> 01:18:52,298
Do not make me threaten you.

619
01:18:52,368 --> 01:18:57,362
We sent her somewhere
where mirrors are forbidden.

620
01:18:58,441 --> 01:19:02,309
- Where the mirrors couldn't find her.
- Where! Where!

621
01:19:03,479 --> 01:19:06,846
St. Augustine's Monastery.
On the road to Reedfield.

622
01:20:09,445 --> 01:20:11,140
How can I help you!

623
01:20:12,581 --> 01:20:14,105
I'm sorry to disturb you. Sister.

624
01:20:14,183 --> 01:20:18,449
But I've come to speak with a member
of your community. Anna Esseker.

625
01:20:18,854 --> 01:20:20,913
Is she expecting you!

626
01:20:21,190 --> 01:20:22,487
No. Not really.

627
01:20:22,558 --> 01:20:25,425
If you're not listed. I cannot help you. Sir.

628
01:20:25,494 --> 01:20:29,590
Can you at least tell her
that I've come from New York

629
01:20:30,166 --> 01:20:31,690
to speak with her!

630
01:20:31,767 --> 01:20:35,032
I work with Dr. Kane
from St. Matthew's Hospital.

631
01:20:35,905 --> 01:20:38,100
It's very important. Please.

632
01:20:44,013 --> 01:20:48,245
St. Matthew's closed down in 1952.
Who are you!

633
01:20:48,317 --> 01:20:50,478
My name is Benjamin Carson.

634
01:20:50,920 --> 01:20:54,720
I work as a night watchman
on Sixth Avenue in New York City

635
01:20:54,790 --> 01:20:58,089
in the building that used to be
St. Matthew's Hospital.

636
01:20:58,160 --> 01:21:00,720
What is it you want. Mr. Carson!

637
01:21:01,130 --> 01:21:02,995
My family is in danger.

638
01:21:03,065 --> 01:21:05,693
And what's threatening them
is asking for you.

639
01:21:05,768 --> 01:21:09,966
I came all this way to ask you

640
01:21:10,039 --> 01:21:12,269
why the mirrors that were left over
from St. Matthew's Hospital

641
01:21:12,341 --> 01:21:14,605
are so desperate to find you.

642
01:21:15,911 --> 01:21:17,640
Please. Miss Esseker.

643
01:21:18,280 --> 01:21:20,043
If you don't help me.

644
01:21:20,116 --> 01:21:22,448
I'm gonna lose the most important thing
to me in this world.

645
01:21:22,518 --> 01:21:24,213
And that's my family.

646
01:21:27,857 --> 01:21:29,791
Sit down. Mr. Carson.

647
01:21:38,868 --> 01:21:41,837
The mirrors are merely windows
on our world.

648
01:21:43,105 --> 01:21:45,972
It is not the wish of the mirrors to find me

649
01:21:47,043 --> 01:21:49,978
but of what is imprisoned inside them.

650
01:21:50,046 --> 01:21:52,139
What is imprisoned inside them!

651
01:21:53,516 --> 01:21:57,043
At the time that I was at St. Matthew's.

652
01:22:00,500 --> 01:22:04,095
Dr. Kane's therapy
for personality disorders

653
01:22:04,170 --> 01:22:09,039
consisted of locking the patient up
in a mirrored room

654
01:22:09,108 --> 01:22:15,274
for several days on end,
forcing them to confront their own image.

655
01:22:17,517 --> 01:22:20,748
Dr. Kane was wrong about his theory.

656
01:22:21,254 --> 01:22:24,951
There is no cure for schizophrenia,
Mr. Carson.

657
01:22:28,060 --> 01:22:30,494
It was something else.

658
01:22:31,163 --> 01:22:37,227
And whatever it was,
it left me and entered the mirrors.

659
01:22:39,105 --> 01:22:40,504
Since that day.

660
01:22:40,573 --> 01:22:44,168
It has been collecting
the souls of the people it kills.

661
01:22:45,211 --> 01:22:47,372
I'm sorry.

662
01:22:47,446 --> 01:22:50,779
But if I agree to go with you
and return back to that place.

663
01:22:50,850 --> 01:22:52,579
I will make it possible for the demon

664
01:22:52,652 --> 01:22:55,519
to cross the threshold
back into the real world.

665
01:22:55,621 --> 01:22:58,146
Do you understand
what that means for my family!

666
01:22:58,224 --> 01:23:01,352
You can't do this.
You need to come back with me.

667
01:23:02,194 --> 01:23:05,163
I'm going to pray for you and your family.

668
01:23:05,231 --> 01:23:08,792
That's all I can do right now. Mr. Carson.
I'm sorry.

669
01:23:10,369 --> 01:23:12,064
God bless you.

670
01:23:13,272 --> 01:23:18,505
Gary Lewis. Terrence Berry and many
other men have died trying to find you.

671
01:23:18,578 --> 01:23:20,773
And because they failed.
Their families died. Too.

672
01:23:20,846 --> 01:23:23,474
Two days ago my sister was murdered.

673
01:23:24,116 --> 01:23:27,142
My family will be next
if you don't help me.

674
01:23:27,587 --> 01:23:28,952
Please.

675
01:23:29,021 --> 01:23:32,252
Please. Wait. Wait.

676
01:23:35,861 --> 01:23:37,294
This is my family.

677
01:23:37,363 --> 01:23:39,263
This is my wife Amy

678
01:23:39,332 --> 01:23:42,096
and my daughter Daisy
and my son Michael.

679
01:23:42,902 --> 01:23:44,597
They're beautiful.

680
01:23:45,071 --> 01:23:48,097
They're innocent.
They've never hurt anybody.

681
01:23:50,209 --> 01:23:51,642
Please.

682
01:23:51,978 --> 01:23:53,468
Take the photo.

683
01:23:54,981 --> 01:23:56,710
Just take the photo.

684
01:24:05,758 --> 01:24:07,248
Look at them.

685
01:24:10,262 --> 01:24:11,729
I'm sorry.

686
01:24:14,233 --> 01:24:16,701
Who the hell do you think you are!

687
01:24:16,969 --> 01:24:18,766
They're just kids!

688
01:24:56,876 --> 01:24:58,275
- Hello!
- Amy.

689
01:24:58,344 --> 01:25:00,938
- Ben. Where are you!
- At the monastery.

690
01:25:01,414 --> 01:25:03,245
- Did you find her!
- Yes.

691
01:25:03,315 --> 01:25:05,340
Yeah! Did you talk to...

692
01:25:05,985 --> 01:25:08,112
- Amy?
- Michael!

693
01:25:09,789 --> 01:25:11,188
Michael!

694
01:25:11,424 --> 01:25:13,585
Ben, hold on, Michael's gone.

695
01:25:13,659 --> 01:25:14,921
- What do you mean!
- I don't know.

696
01:25:14,994 --> 01:25:17,394
I fell asleep with the kids on the bed
and now I don't know where he is.

697
01:25:17,463 --> 01:25:18,521
Michael?

698
01:25:18,597 --> 01:25:19,996
Amy. What's going on!
Is everything all right!

699
01:25:21,467 --> 01:25:22,525
Oh. Fuck.

700
01:25:23,269 --> 01:25:24,827
Amy. What's going on!
Have you got Michael!

701
01:25:26,272 --> 01:25:27,500
Oh. My God.

702
01:25:28,374 --> 01:25:31,002
Ben. There's water everywhere.

703
01:25:32,044 --> 01:25:33,033
Oh. My God.

704
01:25:33,145 --> 01:25:36,842
You've got to be careful of the water.
It creates reflections.

705
01:25:37,650 --> 01:25:39,880
Someone is in the house.

706
01:25:39,952 --> 01:25:41,647
Someone scraped all the mirrors!

707
01:25:41,721 --> 01:25:43,313
Amy. Where is Michael!

708
01:25:43,389 --> 01:25:46,051
I don't know. I don't know where he is.
I don't see him anywhere.

709
01:25:46,125 --> 01:25:47,956
Amy, listen to me,
you've gotta stay away from the water.

710
01:25:48,027 --> 01:25:50,757
Get the kids
and stay away from the water!

711
01:25:51,230 --> 01:25:53,323
- Michael!
- Amy?

712
01:25:53,399 --> 01:25:55,697
Amy! Shit!

713
01:26:04,410 --> 01:26:07,277
Which room is she in! Which one!

714
01:26:11,517 --> 01:26:14,213
My family is not dying tonight.
You are coming with me.

715
01:26:29,068 --> 01:26:30,262
Michael!

716
01:26:48,988 --> 01:26:50,216
Daisy!

717
01:26:53,292 --> 01:26:54,953
Daisy. Come here.

718
01:27:08,974 --> 01:27:10,532
Come here. Daisy.

719
01:27:11,877 --> 01:27:12,935
Mom!

720
01:27:19,451 --> 01:27:20,918
Come here. Sweetheart.

721
01:27:40,606 --> 01:27:42,506
What are you doing in there!

722
01:27:44,443 --> 01:27:46,775
Everything's going to be all right.

723
01:28:00,993 --> 01:28:02,551
No!

724
01:28:05,931 --> 01:28:08,365
No! No!

725
01:28:08,434 --> 01:28:09,594
Daisy!

726
01:28:12,671 --> 01:28:14,730
Come here! Get down!
Get down. Right now!

727
01:28:14,807 --> 01:28:17,742
Get down. Sweetie. Get down.
Oh. My God. Are you okay!

728
01:28:17,810 --> 01:28:21,302
Oh. My God! Stay right there.
Don't move. Baby! Don't move!

729
01:28:21,380 --> 01:28:23,814
- Mom. Why did you do that to me!
- It wasn't me. Sweetheart.

730
01:28:23,883 --> 01:28:25,817
You know I would never hurt you.
You know that.

731
01:28:25,885 --> 01:28:28,217
Here. Hold this. Hold it tight.

732
01:28:29,655 --> 01:28:30,679
Okay!

733
01:28:33,559 --> 01:28:36,926
Here. Get down. Sweetie.
Let me see. Let me see.

734
01:28:38,831 --> 01:28:41,061
Let me see. Sweetie. It's gonna be okay.

735
01:28:41,133 --> 01:28:44,193
All right! I know it hurts. Stay right there.

736
01:28:46,272 --> 01:28:49,708
All right. Give me your hand.
I need you to hold it really tight. Okay!

737
01:28:49,775 --> 01:28:52,300
Just flat and tight. Just like that. Okay.

738
01:28:52,378 --> 01:28:55,677
Now. I need you to listen to me.
Okay. Baby!

739
01:28:55,748 --> 01:28:57,648
- You have to be very brave.
- Okay.

740
01:28:57,716 --> 01:28:59,513
I need you to stay here
no matter what happens.

741
01:28:59,585 --> 01:29:03,146
No matter what you hear. Do not move
from this closet until I come back.

742
01:29:03,222 --> 01:29:04,689
- You understand me. Right!
- Yes.

743
01:29:04,757 --> 01:29:07,555
Okay. Okay.

744
01:29:07,626 --> 01:29:09,753
Do not move. I love you.

745
01:29:11,196 --> 01:29:12,322
Don't move.

746
01:29:40,092 --> 01:29:41,423
Michael!

747
01:29:59,178 --> 01:30:00,475
Michael!

748
01:30:03,649 --> 01:30:04,980
Where are you!

749
01:30:07,419 --> 01:30:08,681
Michael!

750
01:30:26,605 --> 01:30:27,867
Michael!

751
01:30:28,507 --> 01:30:30,668
Michael. What are you doing!

752
01:30:34,847 --> 01:30:39,011
Don't be scared. Mommy.
He just wants to play with us.

753
01:30:39,418 --> 01:30:42,751
Michael. I want you to drop that knife.
Right now.

754
01:30:42,821 --> 01:30:44,345
Do you hear me!

755
01:30:45,424 --> 01:30:49,656
You know very well you're not allowed
to play with knives. Don't you!

756
01:30:51,764 --> 01:30:52,958
Come on.

757
01:30:56,568 --> 01:30:58,297
That's a good boy.

758
01:30:58,670 --> 01:31:00,763
Give me the knife. Michael.

759
01:31:01,373 --> 01:31:03,341
Michael! Michael!

760
01:31:06,412 --> 01:31:07,811
Michael!

761
01:31:15,854 --> 01:31:17,116
Michael!

762
01:31:18,290 --> 01:31:19,621
Michael!

763
01:31:23,328 --> 01:31:24,761
Michael!

764
01:31:26,365 --> 01:31:27,889
Michael.

765
01:31:29,268 --> 01:31:30,599
Michael!

766
01:31:31,403 --> 01:31:34,099
Why are you hiding from me. Sweetheart!

767
01:31:45,751 --> 01:31:47,241
Michael!

768
01:32:39,671 --> 01:32:42,606
You okay! Come on.

769
01:33:29,621 --> 01:33:32,089
It's waiting for me downstairs.

770
01:33:41,400 --> 01:33:45,666
Bring me inside. From now on.
I have to keep my eyes closed.

771
01:33:46,471 --> 01:33:49,269
Step up. You're in the room.

772
01:33:49,808 --> 01:33:51,503
Strap me in.

773
01:34:00,485 --> 01:34:03,215
I spent the darkest days of my life
in this room.

774
01:34:06,291 --> 01:34:07,781
Are you sure there's no other way!

775
01:34:07,859 --> 01:34:10,453
This is for your family. Mr. Carson.

776
01:34:11,830 --> 01:34:13,491
For your family.

777
01:34:27,613 --> 01:34:28,978
Michael!

778
01:35:13,191 --> 01:35:15,455
Michael! Michael. Iook at me.

779
01:35:17,996 --> 01:35:20,760
Michael! No. Michael!

780
01:35:21,266 --> 01:35:25,225
No! Give him back to me! Give him back!

781
01:35:27,005 --> 01:35:28,529
No!

782
01:35:30,042 --> 01:35:32,272
No! Get out!

783
01:35:32,344 --> 01:35:34,312
Come on. Michael!

784
01:35:34,379 --> 01:35:35,744
No!

785
01:35:35,814 --> 01:35:37,475
Please. Please.

786
01:35:39,918 --> 01:35:41,283
You must go now.

787
01:35:41,353 --> 01:35:42,786
Thank you.

788
01:35:43,722 --> 01:35:45,019
No!

789
01:35:49,227 --> 01:35:50,558
Why!

790
01:36:26,198 --> 01:36:28,257
Give him back. Please!

791
01:36:28,333 --> 01:36:31,268
Give him back! Give him back!

792
01:36:32,170 --> 01:36:33,364
Michael!

793
01:36:35,273 --> 01:36:38,709
No! No!

794
01:37:03,135 --> 01:37:04,124
Michael!

795
01:37:04,202 --> 01:37:06,033
Oh. My baby!

796
01:37:31,663 --> 01:37:33,028
Come on.

797
01:37:35,467 --> 01:37:37,697
One. Two. Three...

798
01:37:45,177 --> 01:37:46,804
...five. Six...

799
01:37:49,948 --> 01:37:51,381
Thank God!

800
01:37:56,888 --> 01:37:59,789
Thank you. I love you!

801
01:38:11,870 --> 01:38:12,962
Anna!

802
01:38:41,466 --> 01:38:42,797
Anna!

803
01:40:24,869 --> 01:40:26,769
Come out. You bitch!

804
01:42:38,803 --> 01:42:40,464
Oh. My God.

805
01:42:42,440 --> 01:42:44,169
Oh. My baby.

806
01:42:48,646 --> 01:42:50,273
I love you both.

807
01:42:58,423 --> 01:43:00,050
I love you. Guys.

